revisions:
[{'created': '2019-05-21 05:59:26.000000000', 'message': 'Display quotas per Cinder volume type

A continued work of Mateusz Kowalski (https://review.opendev.org/#/c/511472/), adapted to work with Rocky . Closes-bug: https://bugs.launchpad.net/horizon/+bug/1717342

Change-Id: I6097f523b2ed6d9449a4b00f1c4510663da4dc7f
'}, {'created': '2019-05-21 07:22:04.000000000', 'message': 'Display quotas per Cinder volume type

This patch makes Cinder volume type quotas visible in panels
related to volume creation (from volumes and images tabs).

Currently user is able to select a desired type, but if quotas are
set, there is no way to check if creating a volume is going to
succeed. With this patch two additional quota charts are displayed
so that end user can see if there is still available quota for
selected type.

This is a continued work of Mateusz Kowalski (#511472), 
adapted to work with Rocky.

commit_message:
Display quotas per Cinder volume type

This patch makes Cinder volume type quotas visible in panels
related to volume creation (from volumes and images tabs).

Currently user is able to select a desired type, but if quotas are
set, there is no way to check if creating a volume is going to
succeed. With this patch two additional quota charts are displayed
so that end user can see if there is still available quota for
selected type.

This is a continued work of Mateusz Kowalski (#511472),
adapted to work with Rocky.

Closes-Bug: #1717342
Implements: blueprint quotas-per-cinder-volume-type

Change-Id: I6097f523b2ed6d9449a4b00f1c4510663da4dc7f

Bug Fix : Fail to create Kubernetes VIM

Because, authentication URL is changed since plugin add 'v3'.

commit_message:
Fix sphinx for requirements.txt

According to the lower-constraints.txt [1],
the minimum for sphinx in requirements.txt
should be same as in lower-constraints.txt

This patch fixes the same.

[1]https://github.com/openstack/keystone/blob/6e4d06861e9650b69a5da7f6ae4e19cf64f80fb1/lower-constraints.txt#L59

Change-Id: I6f57f34ff08c581101774a37a297cc635ea4edcc

commit_message:
Use follow: no when creating node_config_directory

For some reason this infinitely recurses when follow=yes (ansible 2.5
and above). Probably something on our end, but work around this
temporarily.

Change-Id: Ibf49e9fe067fba0da99c5c41cd6a5a821ef061f8

commit_message:
Drop v2 registry job and ubuntu-xenial nodeset

The registry service was scheduled for removal in
the S cycle, for that reason we don't need the job
Also we don't have support for xenial anymore so we
are replacing to ubuntu bionic in the nfs job.

Change-Id: Iccb14a8a16af8404e448e3a201e3389bf0356978

commit_message:
Add more channel number for detecting BMC IP address

IPMI SPEC[1] assignment channel number 1-11 for vendors
implementation(We an search "Channel Numbers" in section 6.3).
We met an baremetal product, like H3C, use number 8 as LAN channel.

Current code limit channel number to 1~7,
I think this can increase to 1~11.

[1] https://www.intel.com/content/dam/www/public/us/en/documents/product-briefs/ipmi-second-gen-interface-spec-v2-rev1-1.pdf

Change-Id: I63a6ff91d702b990ef09da13e6e2e269e7274cce
Task: 30654
Story: 2005528
(cherry picked from commit 66d3c8e453a58c01740581079045e9b4368c4bde)

commit_message:
Add support for loading packaged standard registries

Added JsonPackagedFileReader to allow loading JSON from filesystem.

Added licensed Redfish standard message registry files.

Currently, the method to load the files is not intended to be
used by Sushy users, but Sushy will use it internally when
needed in following patches.

Change-Id: Iae206dac90b499614a489fc0e90a0d881f21d310
Story: 2001791
Task: 23062

revisions:
[{'created': '2019-05-21 09:03:31.000000000', 'message': 'Eliminate SQL injection vulnerability in node_cache

In node_cache.find_node() we were constructing a raw SQL query using
unescaped data that came in on the wire. This presented an SQL injection
vulnerability. To avoid this, use the query builder from SQLAlchemy to
ensure that any input strings are correctly escaped.

Change-Id: I2b0ffa307ec1aa57538733f2e454d2d7e994d656
Story: #2005678
Task: 30992
(cherry picked from commit 9d107900b2e0b599397b84409580d46e0ed16291)
'}]
commit_message:
Eliminate SQL injection vulnerability in node_cache

In node_cache.find_node() we were constructing a raw SQL query using
unescaped data that came in on the wire. This presented an SQL injection
vulnerability. To avoid this, use the query builder from SQLAlchemy to
ensure that any input strings are correctly escaped.

Change-Id: I2b0ffa307ec1aa57538733f2e454d2d7e994d656
Story: #2005678
Task: 30992
(cherry picked from commit 9d107900b2e0b599397b84409580d46e0ed16291)

(4 comments)

I was just re-reading the LVM code which suffers the same problem as the Rbd code, and I noticed that there we do the exact same insecure conversion you wanted to add to Rbd:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/727b942a88a812afb7368b4d7d3c314a4f8554ed/nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py#L722-L731

I created convert_images_unsafe following an exploitable instance of exactly the security hole I warned you of. At the time the LVM imagebackend was the only code which was not able to do a safe conversion due to lack of context from the caller. If you read the comment, you'll see that we took the pragmatic approach to audit all current code paths to it and allow it to stand. The context there was that I was refactoring the imagebackend at the time in a manner which meant we could have entirely eliminated this problem by explicitly passing metadata about the disk we were creating to the backend code.

Unfortunately this refactor stalled and did not land, twice, so this problem and many others remain unaddressed. You'll note from the code comment, though, that the security of calling convert_image_unsafe() comes exclusively from a code audit of all calling paths we did at the time, which was a couple of years ago. That code audit is obviously no longer valid, and this code should have been removed long ago.

If I'd thought of this approach at the time, which is to remove the conversion and force the operator to configure force_raw_images = True, we could have removed the only caller of convert_image_unsafe() and deleted the function. Given that we've thought of a safer solution, I think we should do that now. However, as this would require a release note and communication to operators in case anybody needs to update config, we should do it in a separate patch."}, {'account_id': 9555, 'date': '2019-03-04 11:22:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(3 comments)

I think this is the right approach. Please see my comments against patch set 1. You're also going to want some unit test coverage which exercises both the allowed and not-allowed combinations.

We're also going to want to follow this up at some point by making the same change for the Lvm driver. Ideally we'd do it here, but unfortunately we've allowed this for some time so to remove it without warning would be a regression."}, {'account_id': 23498, 'date': '2019-03-04 12:13:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Still needs unit tests, obviously, and I think the release note needs to be much clearer. I've included a suggestion, but feel free to write something better.

I've thought of a problem, though. If the operator previously had force_raw_images = False and changes it to force_raw_images = True, they may have qcow2 files already in the image cache which will now break. The resolution to that would be to just delete them, which we could do automatically in init_host, but this is starting to get a bit complicated. Are you sure you don't want to split the LVM change into a separate patch?"}, {'account_id': 28706, 'date': '2019-03-05 10:40:06.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 28706, 'date': '2019-03-05 10:49:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4: Workflow-1

[{'created': '2019-03-01 08:26:11.000000000', 'message': "Raise error when force_raw_images and images_type are incompatible

Set 'force_raw_images' to 'False'.
Set 'images_type' to 'rbd'.
Use 'qcow2' image format.

If the image format is qcow2, then the temp image file in _base
folder will be qcow2 format. So using command 'rbd import' to import
image file into rbd volume is just to use qcow2 format image.

When using a qcow2 as root disk, the instance is spawned but fails to
boot because data is accessed as raw.

So that the value of force_raw_images and images_type here
are incampatible.

Just raise an error and refuse to start nova-compute service.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686

'}, {'created': '2019-05-05 03:33:17.000000000', 'message': "Fix failure to boot instances with qcow2 format images

Ceph doesn't support QCOW2 for hosting a virtual machine
disk:

  http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/rbd/rbd-openstack/

When we set image_type as rbd and force_raw_images as
False and we don't launch an instance with boot-from-volume,
the instance is spawned using qcow2 as root disk but
fails to boot because data is accessed as raw.

To fix this, we raise an error and refuse to start
nova-compute service when force_raw_images and
image_type are incompatible.
Check and remove the non-raw cache image files when
force_raw_images is True and REQUIRES_RAW_IMPORT is True.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686
"}, {'created': '2019-05-06 06:53:21.000000000', 'message': "Fix failure to boot instances with qcow2 format images

disk:

  http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/rbd/rbd-openstack/

When we set image_type as rbd and force_raw_images as
False and we don't launch an instance with boot-from-volume,
the instance is spawned using qcow2 as root disk but
fails to boot because data is accessed as raw.

To fix this, we raise an error and refuse to start
nova-compute service when force_raw_images and
image_type are incompatible.
Check and remove the non-raw cache image files when
force_raw_images is True and REQUIRES_RAW_IMPORT is True.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686
"}, {'created': '2019-05-14 07:33:15.000000000', 'message': "Fix failure to boot instances with qcow2 format images

Ceph doesn't support QCOW2 for hosting a virtual machine
disk:

  http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/rbd/rbd-openstack/

When we set image_type as rbd and force_raw_images as
False and we don't launch an instance with boot-from-volume,
the instance is spawned using qcow2 as root disk but
fails to boot because data is accessed as raw.

To fix this, we raise an error and refuse to start
nova-compute service when force_raw_images and
image_type are incompatible.
When we import image into rbd, check the format of cache
images. If the format is not raw, remove it first and
fetch it again. It will be raw format now.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686

the instance is spawned using qcow2 as root disk but
fails to boot because data is accessed as raw.

To fix this, we raise an error and refuse to start
nova-compute service when force_raw_images and
image_type are incompatible.
When we import image into rbd, check the format of cache
images. If the format is not raw, remove it first and
fetch it again. It will be raw format now.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686
"}]
commit_message:
Fix failure to boot instances with qcow2 format images

Ceph doesn't support QCOW2 for hosting a virtual machine
disk:

  http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/rbd/rbd-openstack/

When we set image_type as rbd and force_raw_images as
False and we don't launch an instance with boot-from-volume,
the instance is spawned using qcow2 as root disk but
fails to boot because data is accessed as raw.

To fix this, we raise an error and refuse to start
nova-compute service when force_raw_images and
image_type are incompatible.
When we import image into rbd, check the format of cache
images. If the format is not raw, remove it first and
fetch it again. It will be raw format now.

Change-Id: I1aa471e8df69fbb6f5d9aeb35651bd32c7123d78
Closes-Bug: 1816686

commit_message:
Bump tempest role SHA to pull in ping test fix

Pulls in the ping test so that the tempest role will operate
correctly with tests that use 'local' network types, such as
calico.

Change-Id: Ibe9797b8dfd88a8a40501b4154f3c0b5ce0f6268
